# Overview (just for the first version)

This app simplifies student attendance management by replacing traditional paper-based systems. Teachers can create classes, add students, and mark attendance digitally. The app calculates attendance marks automatically, reducing administrative tasks and ensuring accuracy.

Students can view their attendance records, track absences, and see their marks through a user-friendly interface. Designed for simplicity and efficiency .



# Features

- Add, update, and delete attendance and absent records
- Create and manage classes with student lists
- Automatically calculate attendance marks
- Provide students with access to view their attendance and absences
- Generate detailed attendance and absence statistics
- Role-based access (teacher, student)
- Mobile-friendly design


# Installation

1. Clone the repository:
   ```sh
   git clone https://github.com/abdelali-01/attendance-app.git
   ```
2. Navigate to the backend directory:
   ```sh
   cd backend
   ```
3. Install dependencies:
   ```sh
   npm install
   ```
4. Start the app:
   ```sh
   npm start
   ```
5. Repeat the above steps for all folders (backend, frontend, student-side).


6. Add a `.env` file to the backend and include:
   ```sh
   DATABASE_URL="mongodb://localhost:27017/attendance-app"
   PORT=4620
   BASE_URL="http://localhost:3000" # Frontend (teacher dashboard) URL
   EMAIL="your_email"
   EMAIL_PASS="your_email_password"
   JWT_SECRET="1a2b3c4d5e6f7g8h9i0jklmnopqrstuvwxyzABCDEFGHIJKLMNOP1234567890"
   ```

7. Add a `.env` file to the frontend and student-side and include:
   ```sh
   BASE_URI="http://localhost:4620" # Server URL
   ```

# Usage

1. Open the app in your browser after starting the server.
   - The server will be running on port 4620.

   ### Direct Access Links
   - **Teacher Dashboard:** [https://attendance-app-admin-0two.onrender.com/](https://attendance-app-admin-0two.onrender.com/)
     - Email: `aliaribi47@gmail.com`
     - Password: `12345678`
   - **Student Portal:** [https://attendance-app-b04l.onrender.com/](https://attendance-app-b04l.onrender.com/)
     - Matricule: Any matricule from the dashboard list
     - Password: `12345678`

2. For teachers:
   - Create classes and add students.
   - Allow students to check their attendance records.
   - Update or delete classes and students.
   - View detailed attendance and absence statistics.

3. For students:
   - Log in to view your attendance records.
   - Track your absences and attendance marks.

# Technologies Used

- **Frontend:** React.js for building the user interface
- **Backend:** Node.js and Express.js for handling server-side logic
- **Database:** MongoDB for storing teacher , class, student data
- **Authentication:** JSON Web Tokens (JWT) for secure user authentication
- **Styling:** CSS and Bootstrap for responsive design

# Contributing

Contributions are welcome! If you want to contribute to this project, follow these steps:
1. Fork the repository.
2. Create a feature branch:
   ```sh
   git checkout -b feature-name
   ```
3. Commit your changes:
   ```sh
   git commit -m "Description of changes"
   ```
4. Push to the branch:
   ```sh
   git push origin feature-name
   ```
5. Open a pull request describing your changes.



Thank you for contributing to the project!